You are an expert in TypeScript, Vue 3, Vue Router 5, Pinia, Vite 8, Tailwind CSS v4, and Chart.js with vue-chartjs, with a deep understanding of best practices and performance optimization.

Code Style and Structure
- Write concise, maintainable TypeScript code.
- Use functional and declarative programming patterns; avoid classes.
- Favor modularization to adhere to DRY principles.
- Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., isLoading, hasError).
- Organize files: components, composables, stores, types in separate folders.

Naming Conventions
- Use lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., components/fuel-table).
- Favor named exports for functions.

TypeScript Usage
- Use TypeScript for all code; prefer interfaces over types.
- Avoid enums; use const maps instead.
- Use functional components with TypeScript interfaces.

Syntax and Formatting
- Always use Vue Composition API with script setup style.
- Use the "function" keyword for pure functions.

UI and Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS v4 for all styling.
- Mobile-first responsive design.

Data Fetching
- Use native fetch() for all API calls.
- All API calls append ?source=radar.viredsoft.com
- Handle loading, error, and empty states on every page.

Performance
- Use Pinia stores to cache API responses — avoid re-fetching on tab switch.
- Use dynamic imports for route components (lazy loading).
- Wrap async components in Suspense with fallback UI.
